<br>
I see only four points of contention between your chart and mine.  At 2, 8, 66, and 95.  All the other numbers basically match.<br>
<br>
I suspect you were able to get 7 agi and 9 agi but weren't able to force your character to 8 agi without changing equipment.  It's logical to assume that 5 comes between 4 and 6, but with AC it doesn't always work that way.  Note that 12, 18, and 25 are also skipped in what you recorded -- it's because of the 1000/847 part.<br>
<br>
That still leaves 2, 66, and 95 unexplained.  I've never had a level 60 character to test with so it's possibly different, but these are reasonably easy to check.  I've always found that 95 agi gives a different AC than 96 agi, that 65 agi gives a different AC than 66 agi, and that 2 agi gives this same AC as 3 agi.  I encourage you to go back and retest those specific points. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uvendric.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Vendric</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/6/02 9:02:51 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1462.topic&index=23>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: AC Formula found! Now what?</span><hr size=1> Actually I forced exactly every number I listed, even the ones I combined. It took a painfully long amount of time, however, heh... <p><center><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=69400">[60 Grave Lord] Duke Vendric Ravenkrest (Dark Elf)</a></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uvendric.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Vendric</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/6/02 11:39:43 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1462.topic&index=24>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: AC Formula found! Now what?</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://members.bellatlantic.net/~vze26v7m/Images/ACCalculator.zip">Vendric's AC Calculator</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
